AB  - One-dimensional grouped survey data are made available to the public, but the cross-classified data are usually not. Two methods to estimate a contingency table from the known margins are investigated. One method is to fit Goodman's correlation model, and the other is a Bayesian method that incorporates vague, outside information. Both methods are used to estimate a regression model on two or more sets of differently grouped data.
